############################################################

BEGIN_PGML_SOLUTION

[```\newcommand{\amp}{&}
\begin{aligned}
9(30 - H) + 14H \amp= 375\\
270 - 9H + 14H \amp= 375\\
270 + 5H \amp= 375\\
5H\amp=105\\
H\amp=21
\end{aligned}
```]

[```\newcommand{\amp}{&}
\begin{aligned}
C \amp= 30 - H\\
C \amp= 30 - 21 = 9
\end{aligned}
```]

In summary, Desi needs to mix [`21`] pounds of the Honduran coffee beans with [`9`] pounds of the Columbian coffee beans to create this blend.

END_PGML_SOLUTION

